"title": "5216: authority, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5216",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The God-given freedom of action expressed in rightful power to control the actions of others.</p>\n<h2>Ultimate authority belongs to God, who does as he pleases</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:3\">PSA 115:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:6\">2CH 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:12\">JOB 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job23:13\">JOB 23:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:2\">JOB 42:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:6\">PSA 135:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:27\">ISA 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:13\">ISA 43:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9\">ISA 45:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10\">ISA 46:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar acknowledges God's authority</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19-Rom9:21\">ROM 9:19–9:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">EPH 1:11</a> <em>God's authority is demonstrated in election.</em></p>\n<h2>Human authority</h2>\n<h3>All human authority is given and established by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:21\">DAN 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:17\">DAN 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:18-Dan5:21\">DAN 5:18–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:11\">JHN 19:11</a></p>\n<h3>It involves the rightful freedom to give orders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:9\">MAT 8:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:8\">LUK 7:8</a> <em>The centurion to Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:35\">GEN 41:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:20\">NUM 27:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:15\">DEU 1:15</a> <em>Moses delegates authority</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:29\">JDG 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra7:24\">EZR 7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh3:7\">NEH 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth9:29\">EST 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:21\">ISA 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:10\">JER 38:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:23\">MAT 25:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:17\">LUK 19:17</a> <em>the parable of the talents</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:34\">MRK 13:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:20\">LUK 20:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:7\">LUK 23:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:10\">JHN 19:10</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:14\">9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:10\">ACT 26:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:12\">ACT 26:12</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13\">1PE 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>It is limited, unlike God's authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:10-John19:11\">JHN 19:10–19:11</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Responsibilities of those with authority</h2>\n<h3>They are to act as servants, not lording it over people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:25–20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:4-John13:15\">JHN 13:4–13:15</a></p>\n<h3>Their authority is to be used for the benefit of others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:8\">2CO 10:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:10\">2CO 13:10</a></p>\n<h3>It is sometimes necessary to withhold exercising authority for others' good</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:4-1Cor9:18\">1CO 9:4–9:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:1-1Cor6:7\">1CO 6:1–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:8-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:8–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:23-1Cor10:24\">1CO 10:23–10:24</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the authority of believers</h2>\n<h3>Authority over possessions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:4\">ACT 5:4</a></strong> <em>Peter to Ananias regarding the land he sold.</em></p>\n<h3>Authority over the will</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:37\">1CO 7:37</a></strong> <em>Paul on marriage.</em></p>\n<h3>Authority to become children of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The authority of the law over believers during their lifetime</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:1\">ROM 7:1</a></strong></p>",
